FBIS4-41887 "drsov125_a_94026" FBIS-SOV-94-125 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS O. Lobov Talks With Mongolian Counterpart O. Lobov Talks With Mongolian Counterpart PM2806145194 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 28 Jun 94 p 3 PM2806145194 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA Russian BFN [Report by Sergey Sidorov: "Russia and Mongolia: Cooperation in the Security Sphere"] [Text] Regional and international security, the strengthening of Mongolia's nuclear-free status, and the fight against crime, international terrorism, and trafficking in arms and narcotics are the priorities in cooperation between Mongolia and Russia in the security sphere as defined by J. Enhsaihan, secretary of the Mongolian National Security Council, during his visit to Moscow. A joint communique was signed on the results of his talks with Russian Federation Security Council Secretary Oleg Lobov. Questions relating to the settlement of Mongolia's foreign debt and the development of military-technical cooperation were also discussed during the talks. An accord was reached on a return visit to Ulaanbaatar by the Russian Federation Security Council secretary.
